# Code Standards

## Naming Conventions

- **Variables/Functions/Methods**: `camelCase` (`getUserData`, `calculateTotal`)
- **Classes/Components/Interfaces**: `PascalCase` (`UserProfile`, `ApiService`)
- **Interface Prefix**: Start with `I` (`IUserProps`, `IApiResponse`)
- **Constants**: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` (`MAX_ITEMS`, `API_TIMEOUT`)
- **Files/Directories**: `kebab-case` (`user-profile.tsx`, `api-utils/`)
- **Private Methods**: `_privateMethod()` (with underscore prefix)
- **Boolean Variables**: `isActive`, `hasPermission`, `canEdit`

## TypeScript Specifics

- Use interfaces over types for object definitions
- Avoid `any` type - use `unknown` or proper typing
- Use type guards for runtime type checking
- Export types/interfaces from `src/shared/types/`

## React/Next.js Standards

- Functional components only (no class components)
- Custom hooks for business logic (`use` prefix)
- Server Components default, Client Components only when necessary
- Type props with interfaces (`interface ButtonProps`)
- Use `tailwind-variants` for component variants

## Function Design

- **Single responsibility** per function
- **Max 3 parameters** (use objects for more)
- **Verb-named functions**: `calculateTotal()` not `totalCalculator()`
- **Pure functions** when possible (no side effects)
- **Early returns** over nested conditionals
- **Max 50 lines** per function

## Code Organization

- One variable declaration per line
- Declare variables close to usage
- No flag parameters (split into separate functions)
- Max 2 levels of if/else nesting
- Prefer composition over inheritance

## Best Practices

- **DRY**: Extract repeated logic
- **KISS**: Simple solutions over complex patterns
- **YAGNI**: Implement only what's needed now
- **Single Responsibility**: One clear purpose per module
- **Dependency Inversion**: Depend on abstractions

## Comments & Documentation

- JSDoc for public functions/APIs
- Explain "why" not "what"
- Keep comments updated with code changes
- Remove debug/temporary comments before commit
